reviews.review_text:
Cosmic Charlie, St. Steven > NFA > St. Steven Other than that, this is an otherwise forgettable show for me. With a thousand GD and Jerry shows in the collection, the four and five star reviews I see from the soundboard uploads are just too starry-eyed. One SBD reviewer thought the show ran a few clicks slow.  Can't say I notice it.  But I agree with NJPG in another review that there are "some moments of glory, but overall I don't think it's that awesome a show." Another called it "mellow." I wouldn't be so generous. '74 was mellow with that mellow being very intense sometimes.  It's just not here other than the band getting a few sparks flying at the end of the show.  

I like the Cosmic Charlie for the novelty as they played it so rarely. It was a fun and amusing little ditty that surely gave the boyz a chuckle. I also saved it for the fact it was the last one played. And the St. Steven > NFA > Drumz > NFA > St. Steven > Sugar Mag run is good. Being a hard-core Rock & Roller, I've always been a sucker for it. Love '76 for it's widely varied set lists. But other than the above said "moments of glory" to add to the library, there are hundreds of better uploads to be had if you're collecting entire shows.

I've chosen this audience since I'm not impressed with the board.  Adding a significant amount of treble and bass along with cutting the midrange in Soundforge helped tremendously from its "skating rink" hollowness and the overabundance of reverb.  Undoubtedly, Kathy was recording behind or at the board.

With all due respect! Sir! Prior reviewer listen up! While there might be better or more crisper or remastered to quality of an album or some shit and def for this show, I didn’t pick up on you messing with auds and just the show.

I gotta say…I’m stumped. I mean…that guy Dick had GD the Corp control not just release choice shows but hold every piece of evidence they were the greatest band that ever will exist. This is mixed by some of the best tapers that have ever done this. People have no clue why I’m so psyched for a new aud of:
THE SINGLE GREATEST PHIL BOMB THAT GETS FOLLOWED BY ONE OF JERRY’S MUTRON LAVA STREAMS. 

Not fade jam back to Stephen after a brief drum’s. Jerry restores order. Some of the peak you wish you hear every time. Thanks me later. Jerry chills Phil with something you just have to hear. Stephen reprise. Love from Vermont
